[ Level 39 required for Great Cleave faction missions ]
Welcome, I’m James Sexton, a Soulwarden here at Eastburn Outpost.\n\nI'm impressed you made it through; even if there's no bad weather, there's sure to be Corrupted blocking the roads.

Do you have any idea how worried I've been about…oh, you're not her. My apologies. \n\nI'm surprised to see a new face around, our outpost isn't exactly known for casual visits. Especially not in wartime.

Thank you again for recovering Patricia's belongings.

It didn't seem right for some Corrupted husk to carry her Heartgem. It means a lot, to have it back. 

Oh! You’ve reminded me of something.
When I think of Patricia, fallen to Corruption, I get so mad I can't see straight.\n\nIf only there was something I could do to reverse her condition.
Hello {playerName}, I’m Zhen Chang, a Soulwarden assigned to Eastburn Outpost.\n\nHow are you liking the cold? I wish I had stayed home insteading of heading into this snowy waste.
So you've seen the monstrosity called Cleaves Malice?\n\nThe Corrupted were able to build it so quickly because we'd done most of the work for them.
If it's not one thing, it's another.\n\nNo rest for the weary, friend. Not when there's work to be done.

Thank you for collecting all these Heartgems. I know it wasn’t easy. \n\nBut the souls of our friends won’t find rest until we cleanse the Corruption from them. For that, we’ll need to hold a cleansing ritual.
I'm honestly surprised to see you still around. Don't get me wrong, your aid has been invaluable.\n\nBut if I had the choice, I'd be headed home, or at least someplace warmer.
Welcome! I’m Soulwarden Ayize Magoro.\n\nIt does my heart good to see someone new around here. Please, tell me stories of the outside world.
Have you heard the stories, Warden? Beyond Glass Lake there's a blessed hilltop, where Corruption can't take root.\n\nImagine living in such a place, free from Corruption and this infernal war…
Oh, I'm glad to see your face.  {playerName}, we need your help. Something terrible has happened. \n\nIt's Warden Dimka.
May your spirit stay strong in these dark times.\n\nWe can't afford to lose another Soulwarden to Corruption.
Bienvenue! I’m Judithe Owens. I'm a Soulwarden based here in Cleave's Point Outpost.\n\nI'd love to talk to you about where you're from, sometime when you aren't too busy.
You're quite the traveller, aren't you? You've been to quite a few places here in Great Cleave.\n\nHave you managed to make it over to the Eeriedune Graveyard or Misty Borough?
Hello, marhaba, {playerName}. I've been getting some horrifying reports from Capitulum Prime.\n\nSomething strange is going on there, even stranger than those lanterns I had you gather before.
{playerName}, I’ve learned a lot of languages in my time on this earth. There aren’t enough words in any of them to thank you enough for what you’ve done for us here.
We've learned our lesson, like calls to like.\n\nWe won't be storing all the Heartgems of the Corrupted Soulwardens all in one place anymore.

Welcome to Eastburn Outpost, my friend. Soulwarden Dac-Kien Phan at your service.\n\nUnfortunately the war against the Corrupted has prevented us from receiving news from other areas, so you are a welcome sight.
If only you could have seen this place before the war.\n\nStill, it's great to see someone new around here, it means there's still hope!
Oh, there you are. Listen…I was hoping you could do me a personal favor.
You'd best keep yourself safe out there, {playerName}!\n\nWe can't afford to lose any more people around here, moral is low enough as it is.
Be welcome, newcomer. I’m Sauquillo Dimka, a Soulwarden at Cleave's Point.\n\nIf you work hard, you will go far, especially in dark times like these.
I…I can’t let myself think about this right now. Not when there’s so much work to be done.
Hello. Sorry, but I'm not in a talking mood.
Hello, I’m Rymon Knatchbull.\n\nI've been a Ranger in Great Cleave longer than most people have been on living in the outposts.
I've seen you around the outpost, helping the Wardens.\n\nIf you're willing to give us a little more aid, you may be just what we need to turn the tide against the Corrupted.
I thought I'd be seeing you sooner rather than later.\n\nHave you spoken recently with Ranger Madaki?
Hard to stay hidden when carrying a hammer like the Rampant Conviction of Hope.\n\nBut I bet you could do it, if you put your mind to it.
Welcome to Cleave's Point! I’m Ranger Mirrell Law.\n\nJust you wait, we'll be turning the tide against the Corrupted any day now!
Did you know four of our forts are currently held by the Corrupted? Four!\n\nAcedia Bastion, Breakaway Fort, Hollowing Fort, and Nullcavity.
You did a fine job out at Eastburn, really helped them out with their problems.\n\nI've heard something that might be helpful to you.
Just seeing Prime Resolve makes me feel warm inside!\n\nHave you been using it to cleanse the land of the Corrupted? Soon, all of Aeternum will be clean.
Yes, it's really me. I’m Ranger Kayode Balogun, the best Ranger this side of Great Cleave.\n\nThose other Rangers try, but they don't understand what it takes to be the best.
You're making quite a name for yourself, {playerName}.\n\nYou're the adventurer who braved Caminus, in Shattered Mountain!

Ah, I knew it was you!

I can hear the pure tones of Glimmering Mercy ring out as you approach. 

I have to admit, it suits you.
Hi there! I’m Ranger Tibbe Fowler. Have you met my pet rabbit? I'm sure he was around here somewhere…\n\nNo matter how many times I warn him about the dangers he keeps haring off!
You found me, good! I'm often on the move.\n\nWhen Madaki told me about this Corrupted weapon plot, I didn't quite believe her... sounded a bit outlandish, honestly.
Ooo, look at that! You have the Azure Ravager!\n\nI'd love to toss it at the Corrupted and see what it can do.
Welcome to Cleave's Point Outpost {playerName}! I'm Eppie Grace, the proprietor of the Hound and Hammer Inn.\n\nStop by any time you like to get out of the chill.
Don't let the atmosphere around the outpost get you down!\n\nAnytime now we're going to break through the Corrupted and the tide of battle will turn!
Welcome {playerName}! I'm Ingram Kent. I run the Dawn's Light Inn here in Eastburn Outpost.\n\nDon't worry, you can sleep late, no need to be up with the dawn here, even if I am!
You've done us a tremendous favor by letting me know the dispatches weren't getting through.\n\nNow we just have to find out howour messengers were compsomised. Shh.
You've done a lot of good for Eastburn Outpost {playerName}.\n\nNow, don't forget to bundle up before heading out into the cold!
Hello, I'm Master Fisher Eberhart Klaus.\n\nThe fish around here present a challenge like no other. Just like the mountains themselves.
I see you've recently been fishing up treasure chests for Master Abebe. How is he these days?
You've done the Soulwardens a great service with those rations.\n\nNothing like a little fresh fish to spice up their meals.
Welcome to Great Cleave {playerName}. I’m Jennifer Heatly, a Ranger in these parts.
There is something to be said about the different faces of winter.\n\nThe lashing winds of ice, the gentle death of snow.
I can really feel the effects of Rimelash.\n\nI wouldn't want to get too close, there's a icy calm about you that speaks of storms on your horizon.
Are you ready to seek riches and glory?
Indulge not, and remain vigilant. The Covenant is watching. Always
Greetings and well met, fellow Lightbringer. You were involved in that business with Livia Luca, weren't you?\n\nIt's a shame. She was a woman of great faith once. We must always keep vigil.
